To run Digital Image Processor, do the following

1) 'gtkmm 3.0' must be installed in the system. To install it, write the following command in the terminal
sudo apt-get install libgtkmm-3.0-dev

2) Change current directory to the project directory

3) Write 'make' on the terminal

4) A executable 'ImageProcessor' get created in the bin folder in this directory. Run it to run the program.